<h1>Outlines of Some Common Types of Writing</h1>
<h3>Research Papers</h3>
<ul><li>Title
    <li>Author & Affiliation Information
    <li>Abstract
    <li>Introduction
    <li>Background Work
    <li>Methods of Data Collection
    <li>Results
    <li>Discussion & Future Work (also frequently appears in the conlcusion)
    <li>Conclusion
    <li>Acknowledgements
    <li>References
</ul>
<ul>References:
     <ul><li><a href="http://www.cs.columbia.edu/~hgs/etc/writing-style.html">Writing Systems and Networking Articles</a></ul>
</ul>

<h3>Essays</h3>
<ul><li>Introduction
    <li>Supporting Paragraph
    <li>Supporting Paragraph
    <li>Supporting Paragraph
    <li>Conclusion
</ul>
<ul>References:
<ul><li><a href="http://members.tripod.com/~lklivingston/essay/">Guide to Writing a Basic Essay</a>
    <li><a href="http://www.gc.maricopa.edu/English/essay/">Outline of the Five Paragraph Essay</a>
    <li><a href="http://www.aucegypt.edu/academic/writers/">10 Steps to Writing an Essay</a>
</ul></ul>

